Łupowo  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Dźwierzuty, Szczytno County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It is located in Masuria, approximately  west of Dźwierzuty,  north of Szczytno, and  east of the regional capital Olsztyn.
The village was founded by Polish settlers by 1411. As of 1602 the population was almost entirely Polish, and in 1677 it was solely Polish. In 1610, Marcin Dymerski was recorded as the local innkeeper.
